            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Avalanche</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.00)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=24456">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9494">Chris "epic" Moore</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9494&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> A Kybar&#39;s Teeth deck built for speed.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> July 17, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(729)">Targ&#39;n</a><br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(703)">Chogus</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a>ganor, <a href="javascript:card_browser(735)">Hogra Stones</a>)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(731}<a href="javascript:card_browser({900}<a href="javascript:card_browser({903)">Wessig</a></a></a><br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(717)">Sagawal</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(722)">Yebed</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(744)">Jagged Rocks</a>)<br>
T&#39;Lok<br>
(Starting:<a href="javascript:card_browser(702)">Baldar</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(709}<a href="javascript:card_browser({516)">Gia</a>nt <a href="javascript:card_browser(702)">Baldar</a></a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(742)">Ascend</a>)<br>
<br>
Creatures:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(701)">Agrilla</a> x 3<br>
Urigant x 3<br>
Akkar x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(717)">Sagawal</a> x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(702)">Baldar</a> x 1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a>ganor x 1<br>
Karkik x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(476)">Ormagon</a> x 3<br>
<br>
Relics:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(738)">Kybar&#39;s Scroll</a> x 3<br>
Warriors Boots x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(734)">Climbing Staff</a> x 2<br>
Ritual Spears x 2<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(749)">Stone Storm</a> x 2<br>
Crushing Stones x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(744)">Jagged Rocks</a> x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(748)">Rock Slide</a> x 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> x 1<br>
<br>
TOTAL: 41 Cards<br>
<br>
&quot;Avalanche&quot;<br>
By: Epic<br>
Inpired by Matt Loomis (Who Else)   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This is an unbelievably staright forward deck to play.  The magi are book-ended by two high energy magi, with the reset magi, Wessig, in the middle.<br>
<br>
Going first doesn&#39;t seem to matter with this deck with Targ&#39;n and his 17 starting energy, it&#39;s all good.  Play a few creatures and say go (primarily Akkars, Agrilla and Urigants) with Targ&#39;n&#39;s Enhanced Invulneribility, it takes at least a four (3 for the Agrilla) energy creature to hurt these beasts.  The keep to this deck is to KEEP THE OFFENSE GOING. The objective is to pound away on your opponent.  Targ&#39;n usually defeats at least one magi.<br>
<br>
Wessig is there to....umm, well...DIE.  When he dies, all non-Kybar&#39;s teeth cards are discarded (which is all good, with the exception of the off-chance you are playing another KT deck).<br>
<br>
T&#39;Lok is your finisher and with Big Ol&#39; Rock what a finisher.  The objective is wipe the board clean (usually with an Ormie) and then toss the Rock.<br>
<br>
Now, let&#39;s get a little more tricky.  The Ritual Spear is to cycle back through Magi, specifically:<br>
1. Spear Wessig (discarding mass cards from play) and bring back Targ&#39;n.<br>
2. Spear T&#39;lok to Wessig, and Wessig back to T&#39;lok (that is especially rude).<br>
<br>
Kybar&#39;s Scroll is there to help cycle those critical cards you need to finish off your opponent.<br>
<br>
All the spells are all removal and with the energy of Targ&#39;n and T&#39;Lok you are never at a loss for energy.<br>
<br>
Like I said, it doesn&#39;t really take a rocket scientist to understand the concept of this deck although learning what to play when (as with all decks) will take some time.  And to reiterate, this is an offensive based deck, you are essentially bringing it to your opponent till he/she breaks.<br>
<br>
This deck has been really good for me (primarily as players I play with know, I have good card karma with this deck...I have been known to double boots 2 agrillas first turn).<br>
<br>
Another variant is to go: Wessig, T&#39;lok, Bria<br>
It is a bit tricker to play, but basically you try to finish of the game by using Bria to grab 2 Ritual Spears and going Wessig to T&#39;Lok to Big Ol&#39; Rock (huh-huh...I made a rhyme). </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=24456"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24456" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
